              <p>
               -1, 2, and 4
              </p>
            </answer>
        </task>
        
        <task>
          <statement>
            <p>
              For which <m>x</m>-value(s) does <m>f(x)=4</m>. Estimate as needed!
              
            </p>
          </statement>
            <answer>
              <p>
               approximately -0.5, 1, and approximately 4.5
              </p>
            </answer>
        </task>

        
      </activity>

      <activity xml:id="activity-fn-solving">
        
        <task>
          <statement>
            <p> Let <m>h(x)=5x+7</m>. 
              Find the <m>x</m>-value(s) such that <m>h(x)=-13</m>.</p>
          </statement>
            <answer>
              <p>
               <m>-4</m> 
              </p>
            </answer>
        </task>

        <task>
          <statement>
            <p> Let <m>f(x)=x^2-3x-9</m>. 
              Find the <m>x</m>-value(s) such that <m>f(x)=9</m>.</p>
          </statement>
            <answer>
              <p>
               <m>-3</m> and <m>6</m>
              </p>
            </answer>
        </task>

      </activity>

      <activity xml:id="activity-fn-application">
       <introduction>
        <p>
          Ellie has <m>\$13</m> in her piggy bank, and she gets an addition <m>\$1.50</m> each week for her allowance. Assuming she does not spend any money, the total amount of allowance, <m>A(w)</m>, she has after <m>w</m> weeks can be modeled by the function <me>A(w)=13+1.50w</me>. 
        </p>
       </introduction> 
        <task>
          <statement>
            <p> How much money will be in her piggy bank after 5 weeks?</p>
          </statement>
            <answer>
              <p>
               $<m>20.50</m> 
              </p>
            </answer>
        </task>

        <task>
          <statement>
            <p> After how many weeks will she have $<m>40</m> in her piggy bank?</p>
          </statement>
            <answer>
              <p>
               <m>18</m> weeks 
              </p>
            </answer>
        </task>

        <task>
          <statement>
            <p> Let <m>f(x)=x^2-3x-9</m>. 
              Find the <m>x</m>-value(s) such that <m>f(x)=9</m>.</p>
          </statement>
            <answer>
              <p>
               <m>-3</m> and <m>6</m>
              </p>
            </answer>
        </task>

      </activity>

      
    
